#: ../../S/social-science-number.rst:9
msgid ""
"[IBM] A statistic that is :ref:`content-free`\\, or nearly so. A measure "
"derived via methods of questionable validity from data of a dubious and "
"vague nature. Predictively, having a social science number in hand is seldom"
" much better than nothing, and can be considerably worse. As a rule, "
":ref:`management` loves them. See also :ref:`numbers`\\, :ref:`math-out`\\, "
":ref:`pretty-pictures`\\."
msgstr ""
"[IBM] :ref:`content-free`\\ "
"な、あるいはほぼそうな統計値。疑わしく曖昧な性質のデータから、妥当性の疑わしい方法によって導かれた尺度。予測の上では、social science "
"numberを手にしていることは、何もないことよりましであることはめったになく、かなり悪いこともありうる。概して、\\ "
":ref:`management`\\ はそれらが大好きだ。\\ :ref:`numbers`\\ 、\\ :ref:`math-out`\\ 、\\ "
":ref:`pretty-pictures`\\ も参照。"
